cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.DB, cs.VR, cs.IR 

The paper discusses a visualization framework designed for data-heavy visualizations, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR). The framework is also designed to simplify the creation of visualizations, which could fall under databases (cs.DB) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions real-world applications and the potential for virtual reality (cs.VR), further supporting these categories.
